%N A260755 Number of ways to relax the chip-configuration of Anderson et al. one chip at a time.
%C A260755 Terms grow cubic-exponentially but have unexpectedly many small prime factors.
%H A260755 R. Anderson, L. Lov√°sz, P. Shor, J. Spencer, E. Tardos, S. Winograd, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2323970">Disks, balls and walls: analysis of a combinatorial game</a>, Amer. Math. Monthly, 6, 96, pp. 481-493, 1989.
